.TH PRETTY_FILES 1 "July 2026" "pretty_files 1.6.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
pretty_files \- lightweight command-line file viewer with syntax highlighting

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B pretty_files
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <PATHS...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.br

.B pretty_files
.B help

.br

.B pretty_files
.B binary

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B pretty_files
is a lightweight command-line file viewer written in Rust. It displays
text files with syntax highlighting, optional line numbers, recursive
directory traversal, and file filtering.

Syntax highlighting is automatically selected based on the file type.
Files with unsupported or unknown extensions are displayed as plain text.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B help
Display the help menu.

.TP
.B bare
Print file paths without displaying their contents.
Useful for piping file lists into other commands.

.TP
.B binary
Reserved for future binary file support.

.SH READ MODE

Read mode is the default mode and displays the contents of one or more files.

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-numbers
Display line numbers.

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively search directories for files.

.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Print the file name before displaying its contents.

.TP
.B \-D
Disable automatic debug mode.

Automatic debug mode is enabled when multiple files are displayed.

.TP
.B \-S
Disable syntax highlighting.

.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore " " <PATH>
Ignore a file or path. This option may be specified multiple times.

.SS Examples

.TP
Display a file:
.B pretty_files main.rs

.TP
Display multiple files:
.B pretty_files main.rs Cargo.toml

.TP
Display line numbers:
.B pretty_files -n src/main.rs

.TP
Display all files recursively:
.B pretty_files -r src/

.TP
Disable syntax highlighting:
.B pretty_files -S file.txt

.TP
Ignore a file while searching recursively:
.B pretty_files -r -i src/lib.rs src/

.TP
Ignore multiple files:
.B pretty_files -r -i src/lib.rs -i src/main.rs src/

.SH BARE MODE

The
.B bare
command prints file paths without reading or displaying file contents.

.SS Synopsis

.B pretty_files bare
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " " <DIRECTORIES...>

.SS Options

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively list files inside directories.

.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore " " <PATH>
Ignore a file or path while listing files.
This option may be specified multiple times.

.SS Examples

.TP
List files in a directory:
.B pretty_files bare src/

.TP
List files recursively:
.B pretty_files bare -r src/

.TP
Ignore a file:
.B pretty_files bare -r -i src/lib.rs src/

.TP
Ignore multiple files:
.B pretty_files bare -r -i src/lib.rs -i src/main.rs src/

.TP
Use the output in a shell loop:
.nf
for file in $(pretty_files bare -r src/); do
    cat "$file"
done
.fi

.SH BINARY MODE

The
.B binary
command is reserved for future binary file support.

.SH NOTES

.TP
Automatic debug mode is enabled when displaying multiple files.
Use
.B \-D
to disable it.

.TP
The
.B \-r
option expects directories as input.

.TP
Files with unknown or unsupported extensions are displayed as plain text.

.SH DEPENDENCIES

.TP
.B syntect
Provides syntax highlighting and language detection.

.TP
.B walkdir
Provides recursive directory traversal.

